1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,168
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:02,252 --> 00:00:05,922
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:10,593
- <i>♪ Fix it</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:12,846
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:16,224
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:19,019
[Gavin] <i>Is Janine the daughter</i>
<i>Brother Atoy is talking about?</i>

7
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:20,812
Yes, he's the father.

8
00:00:20,895 --> 00:00:22,856
We'll all talk together.

9
00:00:22,939 --> 00:00:24,816
[Karla] <i>What if your Tatoy</i>
<i>already has a child?</i>

10
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:27,444
What kind of question is that?

11
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,904
Then I'd have a sibling.

12
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,322
[Karla] <i>What if you don't like them?</i>

13
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:32,949
If they have a bad attitude?

14
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:36,286
[Ibyang] Tatoy won't tolerate
a bad attitude!

15
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:41,249
Why didn't you tell me
you're the Master Cutter?

16
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:42,625
She told me not to let Janine out.

17
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:44,419
Why? Did the child do something?

18
00:00:44,502 --> 00:00:45,837
Her daddy is outside.

19
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:46,755
PREVIOUSLY

20
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:48,339
My daddy? Who is it?

21
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:51,134
Do you want her
to grow up without a father?

22
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:52,719
You're my daddy?

23
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:55,055
[Janine] <i>But you're also</i>
<i>Ibyang's father, right?</i>

24
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:57,015
<i>I don't like you. I don't want you!</i>

25
00:00:57,098 --> 00:00:58,892
[Red] <i>I don't want you</i>
<i>getting close to him.</i>

26
00:00:58,975 --> 00:00:59,851
I don't like his face.

27
00:00:59,934 --> 00:01:01,478
[in English] Technically,
he's part of the family.

28
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:04,689
[Red] <i>The problem you're avoiding</i>
<i>is the one that comes to you.</i>

29
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:05,857
[Martina] <i>What's the problem?</i>

30
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:08,568
[Mongki] <i>His face is so annoying,</i>
<i>I want to hit him!</i>

31
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:10,361
[Mongki] But Audrey said he's a guest.

32
00:01:11,029 --> 00:01:12,322
How did that happen?

33
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:13,907
[Red] <i>He got my sister pregnant.</i>

34
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:15,950
So even if I don't like it,

35
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:17,660
he's connected to our family.

36
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:19,454
That jerk is so lucky.

37
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:27,378
[music swells]

38
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:30,131
[music fades]

39
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:38,848
Tatoy!

40
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:46,105
- [Atoy] Mmm-hmm.
- [Ibyang] Hmm.

41
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:49,109
Ibyang.

42
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:51,402
Um…

43
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,951
Tatoy has something to tell you.

44
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:01,329
Uh…

45
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:03,206
About what?

46
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:05,250
It's about… uh…

47
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:08,962
Um…

48
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:14,759
About a child and about a father.

49
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:19,597
I also have something to tell you.

50
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:22,142
I made something for you.

51
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:25,562
Can I go first?

52
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:28,940
Uh, oh. Sure! Go on.

53
00:02:35,905 --> 00:02:37,699
"Tatoy, Tatoy!

54
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:40,076
Thank you for the love.

55
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:44,330
Every day, I always feel it.

56
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:47,458
Even if you're not my real father,

57
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:51,629
in my heart, you're the true hero.

58
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:55,466
When there's a game, you're my teammate!"

59
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:58,636
- [sentimental music playing]
- [crowd cheering]

60
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,308
[Ibyang] "When I'm scared or sad,

61
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:06,019
you're always there."

62
00:03:06,102 --> 00:03:08,396
- [dramatic sting]
- [crowd cheering]

63
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:11,774
[Ibyang] <i>"I'm really lucky</i>
<i>to have you, my Tatoy."</i>

64
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:16,279
"Because of you, my life is so happy."

65
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,489
[in English] Thank you.

66
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:21,409
[chuckles softly]

67
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:29,292
- [in English] Wow.
- Did you like it?

68
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:33,296
Of course. [chuckles] Terrific!

69
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,256
[sniffles] It's beautiful!

70
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:39,427
Beautiful. So good.

71
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:40,803
You're so good.

72
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:42,513
You're amazing, child.

73
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,975
I don't like you. I don't want you!

74
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,144
[music fades]

75
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,646
Are you okay?

76
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:51,981
Mmm-hmm.

77
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:55,026
[gentle music playing]

78
00:03:56,444 --> 00:04:00,531
Why does it look like you're crying?

79
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:02,867
I saw you. Oh, oh.

80
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:05,662
You wiped your tears away!

81
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:07,080
‪[Atoy chuckles]

82
00:04:07,163 --> 00:04:09,207
No, that was just…

83
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,000
[sniffles]

84
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:12,669
[chuckles]

85
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:16,089
[grunts] Those are tears of joy!

86
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,384
What do you think, Tatoy?

87
00:04:20,134 --> 00:04:23,388
Was my poem beautiful?

88
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:24,555
Yes, it was beautiful.

89
00:04:25,139 --> 00:04:26,391
You're amazing.

90
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:28,142
Come here. Thank you.

91
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,436
[Ibyang moans softly]

92
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:34,774
‪[Atoy moans softly]

93
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:42,240
[Atoy sighs] This.

94
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:47,245
What were you going to say?

95
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:50,999
Uh, uh… Nothing.

96
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:52,000
[sniffles]

97
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,501
It's nothing.

98
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:54,544
Not now.

99
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,672
Maybe I'll tell you some other time.

100
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,508
- [Ibyang] Ah.
- Mm-hm.

101
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:07,265
Um, Tatoy, my teacher asked, can you…

102
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:09,767
come to our school tomorrow?

103
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:11,936
Tomorrow? Why?

104
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,648
Did something happen to you?
Are you in trouble?

105
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:16,983
- [Ibyang scoffs]
- What did you do?

106
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:19,736
You already think I'm in trouble?

107
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,612
Oh? Then why are we being called?

108
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:27,368
Because the parents
will present what their jobs are.

109
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:28,953
[Atoy] Ah.

110
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:30,830
Okay, fine.

111
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:32,582
All right.

112
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:34,250
I'll go tomorrow.

113
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:35,835
- [sentimental music playing]
- Oh.

114
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:36,753
Huh?

115
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:39,255
- [chuckles]
- Don't cry anymore, Tatoy!

116
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:41,591
Those are tears of joy.
Do you know what that is?

117
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,676
Like when…

118
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:47,388
When you get a new toy?

119
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:51,934
- Don't cry anymore, Tatoy, okay?
- I'm not!

120
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:56,105
[sauve theme music playing]

121
00:06:21,255 --> 00:06:23,049
[music fades]

122
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:25,426
[door clicks open]

123
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:28,846
[Audrey] My child…

124
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:31,641
It's bedtime.

125
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:33,559
That's enough.

126
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:37,522
Fix your things before you go to bed.

127
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:41,943
Child, did you hear me?

128
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:46,114
Nanny will put it away later anyway.

129
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:50,785
Janine.

130
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:53,913
Your mommy told you to do something.

131
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:58,626
[pensive music playing]

132
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:03,589
[Audrey] How did you do that?

133
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:09,554
That's the common dynamics of parents.

134
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,890
The mother is loving and nurturing.

135
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:17,603
The father is the protector
and disciplinarian.

136
00:07:19,355 --> 00:07:21,357
[in English] That's why
Janine needs a father.

137
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:24,527
[tense music playing]

138
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,671
[Gavin] Come on, Karla!

139
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:46,048
Help me with my date with Cathy.

140
00:07:46,924 --> 00:07:49,760
You've been quiet for so long,
I thought you backed out.

141
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:52,805
There's just been lot
of issues at home lately.

142
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:53,806
I'm sorry.

143
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:56,267
But the date is still on.

144
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:57,810
That's why I need your help.

145
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:00,146
Fine!

146
00:08:03,107 --> 00:08:05,359
How's your aunt and Brother Atoy?

147
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:07,278
You know about that?

148
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:08,654
Of course, it's a small world!

149
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:12,200
Wait, that bratty niece of yours?

150
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:14,202
Does she know Brother Atoy is her father?

151
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:15,286
[sighs]

152
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:18,414
Yes, but… their situation is still messy.

153
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:22,210
But at least, Auntie
has a chance to reconcile

154
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:23,961
with Brother Atoy because of Janine.

155
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:28,841
Meanwhile, I'm still hoping
to get close to Cathy.

156
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:31,844
Okay, fine. I'll help you!

157
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:34,972
Okay, okay. But it better be good!

158
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:36,807
Do you remember what I told you before?

159
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:39,060
Something different, something unique!

160
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:40,186
I hope it's like that,

161
00:08:40,269 --> 00:08:43,397
so she'll remember our date as special,

162
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:44,899
and she won't forget me.

163
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:46,859
Is that okay?

164
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,611
[gentle music playing]

165
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:49,612
- [in English] Fine.
- [in English] Yes!

166
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:51,447
[in English] Thank you, Karla!

167
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:54,825
[in English] Thank you, Karla. Thank you!

168
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:57,495
We'll meet later, okay?
I'll call you. Okay?

169
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:01,332
["Sa Wala" by Wickermoss
with Neth Macam playing]

170
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:06,420
♪ <i>Will the heart be made to think</i> ♪

171
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:08,047
[indistinct chattering]

172
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:09,382
[teacher, in English]
Thank you, Mr. Reyes.

173
00:09:09,465 --> 00:09:12,301
Let's applaud Seb and his daddy!

174
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:14,178
[teacher, in English] Thank you!

175
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:15,888
[in English] Who's next?

176
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:19,308
My daddy!

177
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:24,272
[bright music playing]

178
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:28,025
Good day, children.

179
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:29,527
I'm Atoy.

180
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:32,321
Uh, just call me Uncle Atoy.

181
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:35,741
I am a… I am a tailor.

182
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:38,452
Do you know what tailor means?

183
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,162
[students] No, sir.

184
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,126
Good thing you weren't abducted.

185
00:09:45,876 --> 00:09:47,795
My daddy saved me.

186
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:49,005
You have a daddy now?

187
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:52,508
Yes, I do. But I don't like him.

188
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:54,510
Why? Who is your daddy?

189
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:55,636
[somber music playing]

190
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,263
Don't be shocked, okay?

191
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:01,017
- Ibyang's father.
- [both] Him?!

192
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:05,980
But even if you're his daughter,

193
00:10:06,063 --> 00:10:08,232
he's still Ibyang's daddy, right?

194
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:10,735
Because I saw them
together in the classroom.

195
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:12,862
- [stuttering]
- [tense music playing]

196
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:14,697
Wait, he's here?

197
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,991
Then why didn't I see him?

198
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:18,784
And why didn't he come see me?

199
00:10:20,077 --> 00:10:22,496
You said you don't like him.

200
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:25,750
Maybe he only wants Ibyang
to be his daughter.

201
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:29,920
Shut up.

202
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:41,057
So, with every measuring,
cutting, and sewing,

203
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:45,102
my father and I
are truly proud of what we do.

204
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:47,146
We really make it beautiful!

205
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:50,191
We really give it our all.

206
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:51,942
Because, you know,

207
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:56,155
our work reflects the people who wear it.

208
00:10:56,238 --> 00:10:58,074
Right? Just like you students!

209
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:00,201
Oh, look at your uniforms.

210
00:11:00,284 --> 00:11:01,285
See?

211
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:06,666
That symbolizes your school,
your institution. Right?

212
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:09,043
So even for us, parents, everyone here,

213
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:12,630
we wear clothes with honor and dignity.

214
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:16,133
As Tom Ford said-- Do you know Tom Ford?

215
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:17,593
[student 1] No, sir.

216
00:11:17,676 --> 00:11:21,847
Tom Ford, he's an American designer.

217
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:27,645
He said, "Dressing well
is a sign of good manners."

218
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:28,604
Huh?

219
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:33,275
My daddy is amazing, right!

220
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,277
- Isn't he? Isn't he?
- [student 1] Yes!

221
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,863
[Janine] He's just your pretend daddy.

222
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:39,198
[pensive music playing]

223
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:42,910
- Janine.
- [thud]

224
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:45,704
I am his real child.

225
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:47,456
You're just adopted, Ibyang.

226
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:48,999
Right, Daddy?

227
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,754
[music swells]

228
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,886
So don't act like you're his child!

229
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:03,389
You're not my daddy's real daughter.

230
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:05,391
That's not true!

231
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:07,643
You're lying again.

232
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:10,354
Teacher, she's causing trouble!

233
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,356
And she doesn't even belong here.

234
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:15,776
[in English] Janine,
please go back to your classroom.

235
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,862
I'm just telling the truth.

236
00:12:17,945 --> 00:12:20,072
Daddy even went to our house yesterday

237
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:22,408
to talk to Grandpa and my mommy.

238
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,161
If you don't want to believe me,
then ask him yourself.

239
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:29,039
Ibyang.

240
00:12:30,207 --> 00:12:32,293
Come outside. Let's talk first. Come on.

241
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:35,629
[in English] Excuse me. Ibyang.

242
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:36,797
[Atoy, in English] Teacher, excuse us.

243
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:40,092
‪[unsettling music playing]

244
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:52,897
Ibyang.

245
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:56,150
[music fades]

246
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:03,282
Is what Janine said… true?

247
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,619
Ibyang, that's what

248
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,622
I wanted to tell you last night.

249
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:13,250
It's true.

250
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,377
[somber music playing]

251
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,046
Janine is my child.

252
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:24,345
But why didn't you tell me right away?

253
00:13:28,724 --> 00:13:30,017
Because…

254
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,230
I didn't know how to tell you,

255
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,398
because…

256
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:41,195
I didn't want to hurt you.

257
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:48,285
But I still got hurt.

258
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,041
[in English] I'm sorry, Ibyang.

259
00:13:56,126 --> 00:14:00,214
You know, I only found out recently.

260
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:02,299
And…

261
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:08,597
I just didn't know how to tell you.

262
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:11,183
[in English] I'm sorry.

263
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:15,229
Why is it unfair?

264
00:14:17,856 --> 00:14:23,237
Teacher taught us to always be honest.

265
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:28,158
But why weren't you honest with me?

266
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:35,207
- Ibyang. Ibyang!
- [sobs]

267
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:39,044
[melancholic music playing]

268
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:40,129
[Atoy] Ibyang!

269
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:04,028
[music fades]

270
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:17,583
[gentle music playing]

271
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:36,268
I know you're angry with me.

272
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:41,565
Uh…

273
00:15:43,984 --> 00:15:45,110
I'm sorry.

274
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:50,074
I'm not angry with you.

275
00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:54,578
And it's not your fault.

276
00:15:57,748 --> 00:16:01,043
You said you didn't know, right?

277
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:02,586
[Atoy] Yes!

278
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:04,463
I really didn't know.

279
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:10,469
You said you're not angry, but…

280
00:16:10,552 --> 00:16:11,512
[clicks tongue]

281
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:13,514
Why are you crying?

282
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:20,229
Because…

283
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:23,565
If you really do have a child…

284
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:27,361
maybe…

285
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,990
you won't adopt me anymore,

286
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:35,619
because you love Janine now.

287
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:40,082
Who told you that?

288
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:44,586
Oh, Ame. She's so talkative!

289
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,297
I heard you talking.

290
00:16:47,965 --> 00:16:50,009
Ibyang, listen to me, okay?

291
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:53,721
Just because I have a real daughter,

292
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:57,474
that doesn't mean
I won't fulfill my promise to you.

293
00:16:58,892 --> 00:16:59,935
[Atoy] Hmm?

294
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:02,938
Because I will still do it.

295
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:06,066
I will still keep my promise to you.

296
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:07,901
I will be your father.

297
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,446
- Really?
- [Atoy] Yes.

298
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,864
Then I love you both.

299
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:14,074
Of course I love Janine too.

300
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:16,744
I love you both.

301
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:18,871
Okay?

302
00:17:24,084 --> 00:17:26,086
I'm not sad anymore.

303
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:29,089
I'm happy again.

304
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:30,299
Really?

305
00:17:35,429 --> 00:17:40,059
[sentimental music playing]

306
00:17:57,785 --> 00:18:00,162
- Don't hug him!
- [Ibyang] Ouch!

307
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:01,580
[sinister music playing]

308
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:02,956
[Atoy] Janine.

309
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,416
Why are you hugging him?

310
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:06,794
He's not even your daddy!

311
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:09,379
[Atoy] Janine, don't be like that.

312
00:18:10,005 --> 00:18:12,007
Even if she's not really my own blood,

313
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:14,676
I still treat her like my real daughter.

314
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,305
I love you both.

315
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:20,724
You're both important to me.

316
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:23,185
[music fades]

317
00:18:23,268 --> 00:18:24,228
[Atoy] Okay?

318
00:18:25,312 --> 00:18:26,313
[in English] Okay, Daddy.

319
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:28,941
[somber music playing]

320
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:30,692
You called me Daddy?

321
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:33,612
[chuckles]

322
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:37,199
‪[mutters]

323
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:39,118
So that means
you accept me as your father?

324
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:42,704
[pensive music playing]

325
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:44,540
Can I hug you?

326
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:54,883
[gentle music playing]

327
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:57,886
All right, I'll allow it.

328
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:02,141
But you have to love me more than Ibyang.

329
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:03,809
Okay?

330
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:06,895
‪[dramatic sting]

331
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:08,981
‪[dramatic sting]

332
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,301
[Emerson] <i>Unbelievable.</i>

333
00:19:37,384 --> 00:19:41,597
But you know, his biggest mistake
was when he dropped his gun.

334
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,723
Yes!

335
00:19:42,806 --> 00:19:45,809
When Red dropped the gun,
that's when Atoy struck.

336
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,561
He hit him! He dropped him.

337
00:19:47,644 --> 00:19:49,271
Then… [blabbering]

338
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:50,189
[explosive sound]

339
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:52,274
He really beat him up!

340
00:19:52,357 --> 00:19:54,151
So, it was very intense.

341
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:57,404
We really felt the intensity, brother!

342
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:58,989
It was like it pierced straight through.

343
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:01,074
- Like an action scene, right?
- Yes, that's it. Exactly!

344
00:20:01,158 --> 00:20:02,659
- You know, you could do it!
- [Emerson] I could.

345
00:20:02,743 --> 00:20:03,744
[Emerson] I could, right?

346
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:04,786
I could star in an action series.

347
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:07,748
You could be an extra.

348
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:11,960
Those guys who get killed
by the enemy's boss

349
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,128
because they failed.

350
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,379
- Look at how mean you're being.
- Hmm-mm.

351
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:15,589
Oh, you're making fun of me.

352
00:20:15,672 --> 00:20:18,133
You lack a lot of things…

353
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:20,093
But what you have a lot of

354
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:22,471
are insults towards me!

355
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:24,348
I'm just joking, come on!

356
00:20:24,431 --> 00:20:26,516
- Gee! Oh, sorry.
- [laughter]

357
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:29,144
So that's why Janine is like that, right?

358
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:32,481
Because she has a relative who's a demon!

359
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:34,233
- Mmm-mmm.
- It's that Red, you know?

360
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:37,778
I have a feeling his birth certificate
is registered in hell.

361
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:40,572
But at least, he didn't win against Atoy.

362
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:46,703
And I saw Atoy's determination
to get to know his child.

363
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:49,623
Because he faced Audrey's father.

364
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:54,920
But I wish, brother,
he also prepared Ibyang.

365
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:57,381
I feel bad for her.

366
00:20:57,464 --> 00:20:59,508
She deserves to know everything, right?

367
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:02,094
Come on.

368
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:04,221
It's like you don't even know Atoy.

369
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:05,973
I'm sure…

370
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:08,976
he won't let his foster child get hurt.

371
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:11,979
[pensive music playing]

372
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:14,022
I already talked to your teacher.

373
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:17,484
She'll talk to your classmates herself so…

374
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:20,362
they won't ask you questions anymore.

375
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:21,989
I'll take care of that, okay?

376
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,699
Let's go home.

377
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,368
Daddy!

378
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,912
Can you take me home?

379
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:31,957
Um, then let's stay in the house first.

380
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,333
There's a swimming pool there.

381
00:21:34,042 --> 00:21:37,587
We can go swimming. Come on. Please?

382
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:39,881
[in English] Please?

383
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:44,636
- [tense music playing]
- [dramatic stinging]

384
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:51,059
[in English] Please, please, please!
Please, Daddy?

385
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:52,978
[Atoy] Uh…

386
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:54,771
[Janine] Why?

387
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:57,691
I thought you wanted to be with me?

388
00:21:57,774 --> 00:21:59,693
Uh, ye-- yes, of course.

389
00:21:59,776 --> 00:22:03,071
It's just that, um, I haven't asked
permission from your mommy yet.

390
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:05,032
And from your grandpa.

391
00:22:05,115 --> 00:22:09,202
I can't suddenly just go to your house
and just hang out there.

392
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:11,413
[pensive music playing]

393
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:12,622
[Atoy] Don't worry.

394
00:22:13,498 --> 00:22:14,875
As long as your mommy agrees,

395
00:22:15,459 --> 00:22:17,252
I'll come visit you there.

396
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:19,713
And then we can even go out afterwards.

397
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:21,214
Okay?

398
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:25,177
All right?

399
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:31,183
[unsettling music playing]

400
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:36,229
Let's go.

401
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:47,824
[music fades]

402
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:50,077
I was surprised.

403
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,495
She called me…

404
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,330
"Daddy".

405
00:22:53,413 --> 00:22:55,165
[deep breath]

406
00:22:55,957 --> 00:22:57,793
It feels different, Mom.

407
00:22:58,543 --> 00:22:59,544
It's like…

408
00:23:00,128 --> 00:23:02,714
You know, like there's…

409
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:06,259
a thrill you can't explain… Whoo.

410
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:08,053
It's obvious from your smile, brother.

411
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:09,763
It reaches up to the sky!

412
00:23:09,846 --> 00:23:12,099
So, how's Ibyang?

413
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:14,142
Ibyang?

414
00:23:14,226 --> 00:23:15,185
Well…

415
00:23:15,936 --> 00:23:18,772
At first, she was sad.

416
00:23:18,855 --> 00:23:23,610
But I explained to her
that no matter what happens,

417
00:23:23,693 --> 00:23:27,614
I won't change the way I treat her,
that I'll still be here for her.

418
00:23:27,697 --> 00:23:28,990
That's it.

419
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:31,868
That's good then.

420
00:23:31,952 --> 00:23:34,079
I'm happy for you, Atoy.

421
00:23:34,162 --> 00:23:36,039
[gentle music playing]

422
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:39,167
I am really happy.

423
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:43,964
But is that really the only reason
you're this happy?

424
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:48,969
Maybe there's still a chance
for you and Audrey to get back together,

425
00:23:49,052 --> 00:23:50,345
that's why you're like this.

426
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:53,223
Get back together-- Hey, no.

427
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:56,518
No way. This is really just for our child.

428
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:58,478
And besides, it's over.

429
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,063
I have no interest in her anymore.

430
00:24:00,147 --> 00:24:03,066
You guys, stop teasing me about that.

431
00:24:03,692 --> 00:24:04,901
[music fades]

432
00:24:04,985 --> 00:24:05,986
[birds chirping]

433
00:24:06,653 --> 00:24:08,572
[Audrey, in English] Yes.
That's definitely her.

434
00:24:08,655 --> 00:24:09,948
Ah, Janine!

435
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:12,993
[giggles, in English]
How was your day, dear?

436
00:24:13,577 --> 00:24:15,162
- [in English] Tell me about it.
- [Janine] Mommy.

437
00:24:16,246 --> 00:24:18,039
I want to go to my daddy.

438
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:21,209
[in English] What?

439
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:22,836
I thought you didn't like him?

440
00:24:22,919 --> 00:24:24,754
Not anymore. We're okay now.

441
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:27,966
Just drop me off at Daddy's house.

442
00:24:28,049 --> 00:24:29,342
It's Friday anyway.

443
00:24:29,968 --> 00:24:31,720
Pick me up on Sunday.

444
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:33,597
No, you can't.

445
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:35,724
[mysterious music playing]

446
00:24:35,807 --> 00:24:36,808
Why not?

447
00:24:37,475 --> 00:24:39,019
He's my daddy.

448
00:24:39,644 --> 00:24:41,897
[in English] Because I said so, dear.

449
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:43,190
You're so selfish!

450
00:24:44,774 --> 00:24:46,526
I just want to be with my daddy.

451
00:24:47,235 --> 00:24:48,445
[in English] I hate you, Mommy!

452
00:24:48,528 --> 00:24:50,822
If you don't let me,
I don't want you anymore!

453
00:24:50,906 --> 00:24:52,532
[in English] Don't talk to me like that.

454
00:24:56,703 --> 00:24:57,537
‪[sighs]

455
00:24:58,205 --> 00:24:59,289
[music fades]

456
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:01,124
What should I do with that child?

457
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:04,544
You know, Auntie, in the short time

458
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:06,129
I got to know Brother Atoy,

459
00:25:06,713 --> 00:25:08,798
I feel like he can discipline Janine.

460
00:25:09,466 --> 00:25:11,551
He's a good father to Ibyang.

461
00:25:11,635 --> 00:25:15,263
[rousing music playing]

462
00:25:18,475 --> 00:25:24,439
[electronic blipping]

463
00:25:24,522 --> 00:25:25,690
[tense music playing]

464
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:27,901
Atoy is lucky to have you as a girlfriend.

465
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:29,861
Ah, girlfriend? No, they're not together!

466
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:31,988
Ms. Audrey, she's not with Atoy.

467
00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:33,657
Tonet is just hoping.

468
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:34,783
Mm-mm.

469
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:35,742
[Janine] <i>Hi, Ibyang!</i>

470
00:25:35,825 --> 00:25:36,743
‪UP NEXT

471
00:25:36,826 --> 00:25:38,703
What are you doing here?

472
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:40,872
Janine is staying here for the weekend.

473
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:42,415
[Cita] <i>How are the kids?</i>

474
00:25:42,499 --> 00:25:44,751
They seem to be getting along.

475
00:25:44,834 --> 00:25:47,629
I really hope they treat each other
like sisters.

476
00:25:47,712 --> 00:25:51,675
I thought you came here
because we're okay now.

477
00:25:51,758 --> 00:25:53,051
I just said that.

478
00:25:53,134 --> 00:25:55,553
You know, you shouldn't be here.

479
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:56,721
You're the one who should leave. Go!

480
00:25:56,805 --> 00:25:58,139
Get out! Leave!

481
00:25:58,223 --> 00:25:59,474
Why?

482
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:02,477
- [Janine] Leave, leave!
- Why?

483
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,937
- [Janine] Leave, leave!
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

484
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:06,064
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

485
00:26:06,147 --> 00:26:09,526
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

486
00:26:09,609 --> 00:26:10,944
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

487
00:26:11,027 --> 00:26:12,946
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
